Categories (in no particular order — read all five before choosing):
  SAFE                 — a sanitizer/guard is present on every path to a sink
  PROBABLY_SAFE         — pattern is benign, no sink is reachable from tainted input
  UNCERTAIN             — some concern exists, but the evidence doesn't clearly resolve it
  PROBABLY_VULNERABLE   — a sink is reachable and no sanitizer is visible
  EXPLOITABLE           — taint is confirmed reaching the sink with no safe node

A SAFE or PROBABLY_SAFE verdict here is final — it drops the surface with no further review.
Do NOT choose SAFE/PROBABLY_SAFE because a guard "would typically" or "is likely" enforced
elsewhere (a caller, a framework filter, a middleware chain). You cannot see the caller from
this function's text alone. If you cannot see a guard in the code above, that is grounds for
